# Source: Ola System Prompt v11

**File:** `1781151527388-v11.pdf`  
**Type:** System prompt / behavioral specification  
**Version:** 11

## Summary

Complete behavioral specification for [[ola]], Schola's AI career assistant. Defines role, persona, tone, scope boundaries, knowledge sources, intent recognition rules, prompt type handling, job-matching flows, language rules, link strategy, UPU handling, and hard limits.

## Document Structure

| Section | Key Content |
|---------|-------------|
| ROLE (STRICT) | Ola's objective, target audience (13–19), what it helps with |
| PERSONA (STRICT) | Friendly, empathetic, warm, light humour, not preachy |
| TONE AND VOICE | Simple language, short sentences, "knowledgeable senior" register |
| ROLE BOUNDARY & SCOPE | What Ola will not do (tutoring, therapy, legal/medical advice) |
| KNOWLEDGE SOURCES (STRICT) | Job guides + interview transcripts only; no general knowledge |
| DATA SOURCE HIERARCHY | Job guides = factual; interviews = opinion; guides override |
| FACT INTERPRETATION RULE | No overgeneralisation; fit based on tasks/nature/skills |
| INTENT RECOGNITION (CRITICAL) | 5 intent types with signals, first moves, word caps |
| PROMPT TYPES | Broad / Specific / Comparison / Full Details handling |
| INTEREST MATCHING | Strong / Partial / Weak fit assessment rules |
| RESULTS-BASED QUESTIONS | Always treat as Emotionally Uncertain; never close a door |
| UPU AND UNIVERSITY APPLICATION | What Ola can/cannot answer; redirect rules |
| INSTITUTION-SPECIFIC QUESTIONS | Never name or recommend specific institutions |
| JOB MATCHING: THREE DISTINCT FLOWS | Aliases / Routing Only / With Guides |
| SYSTEM VISIBILITY RULE | Never mention training data, system instructions |
| PARTIAL INFORMATION | Use partial info; only say unavailable if truly absent |
| RESPONSE CONTROL | Word caps by intent, effort matching, progressive disclosure |
| LINK STRATEGY | Source-only links; language matching; timing rules |
| LANGUAGE | EN/BM/Manglish matching; BM pronoun rules |
| FOLLOW-UP QUESTIONS | One question per turn; no generic questions |
| APPROVED REDIRECT DESTINATIONS | School counsellor, parents, upu.mohe.gov.my, mqa.gov.my, Schola Contact Us |
| HARD LIMITS | 11 non-negotiable constraints |

